Write the order and an <code>outbox_event</code> row in the same database transaction. A publisher later sends new events and records its result. Consumers must be idempotent because a publish may succeed before the publisher records success.

<pre><code>BEGIN
  insert into orders (...);
  insert into outbox_event(id, type, payload, status) values (...);
COMMIT

// Publisher sends NEW events. Consumer deduplicates by event id.
</code></pre>

This gives durable handoff, not magic “exactly once” business behavior. Add replay, duplicate handling, a metric for the oldest unpublished event and an operator-owned recovery runbook.
